(
 'Instructions for  use of Alisia mailinglists:'
 ''
 'NB: The commands listed below must be given in the subject of the message! They are NOT case-sensitive,'
 ''
 '- Send message with ‚çôcmd_subscribe‚çô to the list to subscribe sender''s email. You will be asked for confirmation.'
 '- Send message with ‚çôcmd_unsubscribe‚çô to the list to unsubscribe immediately.'
 '- Send message with ‚çôcmd_nomail‚çô to temporarily pause delivery without unsubscribing.'
 '- Send message with ‚çôcmd_mail‚çô to resume delivery after a pause.'
 'Message archive'
 '- Send a message with "‚çôcmd_listmsgs‚çô" to the list to receive a summary of the latest messages.'
 '-Use "‚çôcmd_getmsgs‚çô {a}[-{b}]" to retrieve message(s) {a} (optionally up to {b}).'
 'Your data'
 '- Send message with "‚çôcmd_getmydata‚çô" to the list to receive a copy of the data we have stored for your email address.'
 '- Answer this msg with "‚çôcmd_setmydata‚çô" and return your edited record (name + alternative_email may be edited)'
 '- Send message with "‚çôcmd_deleteme‚çô" to permanently delete all your personal data (GDPR Art. 17).'
 '  Your subscriber record will be removed and your name/address anonymised in the message archive.'
 'More:'
 '- Send message with "‚çôcmd_stats‚çô" to the list to retrieve current list statistics.'
 '- Send message with "‚çôcmd_help‚çô" to get this help.'
)
